<taxonomicName authority="Huo &amp; Du" authorityName="Huo &amp; Du" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,556,959,986]" class="Insecta" family="Perlodidae" genus="Perlodinella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibetensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,419,959,986]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Perlodinella tibetensis</emphasis>
Huo &amp; Du
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[564,658,960,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1031,1166]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,316,1031,1057]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Adult habitus</emphasis>
: General body color dark brown to black (
<figureCitation box="[797,890,1031,1058]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1857,1881]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,1198,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-119@6.[169,1418,1190,1834]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 12. Perlodinella tibetensis Huo &amp; Du sp. nov., male habitus. A: the smaller individual, dorsal and ventral; B: the larger individual with distinct tergal spots, dorsal and ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810253/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Figs. 12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[903,934,1032,1058]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1684,1708]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,939,1654]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[167,1421,931,1661]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 17. Perlodinella tibetensis Huo &amp; Du sp. nov., female habitus.A: macropterous; B: the sole brachypterous individual from Meiduo, Coqen County." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810263/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">17</figureCitation>
). Triocellate, anterior ocellus small, distance between posterior ocelli almost equal to width of the eyes. Head black, with a small yellowish spot around each ocellus and an oval yellowish spot between the posterior ocelli. Pronotum black with pale rugosities, without any median stripe (
<figureCitation box="[318,411,1139,1166]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="7.[151,250,774,798]" captionTargetBox="[157,1420,184,746]" captionTargetId="figure-30@7.[154,1433,181,749]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 13. Perlodinella tibetensis Huo &amp; Du sp. nov., male. A–B: head and pronotum (newly emerged/body sclerotized); C: forewing; D: hindwing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810255/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Figs. 13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[423,454,1140,1166]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1957,1981]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,1507,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-55@11.[156,1432,1505,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 19. Perlodinella tibetensis Huo &amp; Du sp. nov., female, head and pronotum. A–B: yellow spot inverted triangular; C–D: yellow spot oval." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810269/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">19</figureCitation>
). Legs brownish. Abdominal segments dark brown to black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6810253" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6810253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6810253/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384" startId="6.[151,250,1857,1881]" targetBox="[175,1410,1198,1826]" targetPageId="6">
